<hr data-index="5326">
<section id="c17-sec-0039" data-index="5327">
<h2 data-index="5328"><span class="codeColorBlue3" data-index="5329">Disclosure of Fair Values: Impaired Assets or Liabilities</span></h2>
<p data-index="5330">In addition to financial instruments, companies often have assets or liabilities that are remeasured on a nonrecurring basis due to impairment. In this case, the fair value hierarchy can highlight the reliability of the measurement, coupled with the related gain or loss for the period. <a class="blue" id="c17-fig-0049-1" href="#c17-fig-0049" data-index="5331" data-section-index="27" data-section-idref="c17-fig-0049" data-target-data-index="5333"><b data-index="5332">Illustration 17B.4</b></a> highlights this disclosure for McClung Company.</p>
