<p id="c17-ex-0033" data-index="6992"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="6993"><b data-index="6994">E17.20</b></span> <span class="red" data-index="6995"><b data-index="6996">(LO <a href="#lo_2" data-index="6997" data-section-index="27" data-section-idref="lo_2" data-target-data-index="1513">2</a>, <a href="#lo_4" data-index="6998" data-section-index="27" data-section-idref="lo_4" data-target-data-index="2322">4</a>)</b></span><b data-index="6999"> (Fair Value Measurement Issues)</b> Assume the same information as in <a href="#c17-ex-0032" data-index="7000" data-section-index="27" data-section-idref="c17-ex-0032" data-target-data-index="6925">E17.19</a> for Lilly Company. In addition, assume that the investment in the Woods Inc. stock was sold during 2021 for $195,000. At December 31, 2021, the following information relates to its two remaining investments of common stock.</p>
